data.text:
1. Have a Julep ( a bourbon cocktail) and listen to Jazz at Kansas Smitty’s bar in London’s Broadway market. There are eight Juleps to choose from! 2. Book tickets for Mrs Henderson presents at the Theatre Royal Bath. The show respect runs from 15th August to 5th September and stars Tracie Bennett. The lyrics have been written by world acclaimed lyricist, Don Black.

3. Spend the day at BeachEast with family and friends building sandcastles, having fun at the fair and enjoying seaside snacks in the Stratford sunshine. BeachEast will bring the seaside to the city this summer at Queen Elizabeth Olympic Park the home of the London 2012 Olympics and Paralympics. The beach is open July 11 – August 31, 2015

4. Have a breakfast Kebab at Chifafa. This kebab has been created by Masterchef: The Proffesionals runner up Sven Hanson Brit. Chifafa can be found 45- 47 Clerkenwell road, London. The kebab is served between 8 and 10.30 in the morning.
